aiden was my favorite film of the year, if you like a korean costume sadomasochistic lesbian thriller (which I am sure you do), you are gonna love this one. <br /><br />Besides, in a previous film director Chan Park Wook gave me the 2nd greatest Katharsis moment in my life. Can you guess which one stays nr1, George?","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"February 1 2017, 05:29:59 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Thank you for the recomendation.","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://www.facebook.com/app_scoped_user_id/1029760507091186/","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Matheus Ervall","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_3468327","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=77306602&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Matheus Ervall","ctime_ts":1485926999,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/125768290/77306602","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25711907#t25711907","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25711907#t25711907","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25711907#t25711907","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_3468327","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://www.facebook.com/app_scoped_user_id/1029760507091186/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25711907,"talkid":100437,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25711907#t25711907","above":25702435,"upictitle":"Matheus Ervall: pic#125768290","article":"Just watched it, really fascinating movie. Now I need to read something by Wolfe, maybe I should have begun the other way around?","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"February 2 2017, 00:39:34 UTC","parent":25702435,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Thank you for the recomendation.","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://www.facebook.com/app_scoped_user_id/1029760507091186/","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Matheus Ervall","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_3468327","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=77306602&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Matheus Ervall","ctime_ts":1485995974,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/110588672/274575","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25706275#t25706275","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25706275#t25706275","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25706275#t25706275","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"mallorys_camera","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://mallorys-camera.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25706275,"talkid":100415,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25706275#t25706275","upictitle":"Every Day Above Ground: pic#110588672","article":"Interesting.  I hated <i>Genius</i> with the hatred of a million white burning suns!<br /><br />Movies about writers are pageants where the hoariest clichés parade about in ill-fitting swimsuits. Since very few people actually read anymore, prospective audience members are unfamiliar with the biographical subjects except as cultural tropes. There’s always this sense that you’re watching a cowboy movie or a medieval romance or some other depiction of the standard bearers of some lost civilization. <br /><br />Genius is filmed entirely in sepia – just in case you’re too stupid to pick up that its subtext is Depression-era New York City. Maxwell Perkins never takes off his hat. <br /><br />And was the relationship between Thomas Wolfe and Maxwell Perkins somehow more important than, say, the relationship between Scott Fitzgerald and Maxwell Perkins, or the relationship between Ernest Hemingway and Maxwell Perkins?","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"February 1 2017, 16:21:27 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://mallorys-camera.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"mallorys_camera","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"mallorys_camera","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://mallorys-camera.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"mallorys_camera","ctime_ts":1485966087,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25708579#t25708579","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25708579#t25708579","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25708579#t25708579","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25708579,"talkid":100424,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25708579#t25708579","above":25706275,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"I loved that Perkins never took off his hat.<br /><br />Was Wolfe more important to Perkins than Fitzgerald or Hemingway?  You can certainly make that argument.  He was the problem child, and their relationship was more tumultuous and troubled than the others... which makes it inherently more dramatic.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"February 1 2017, 18:44:51 UTC","parent":25706275,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1485974691,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/110588672/274575","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25709603#t25709603","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25709603#t25709603","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25709603#t25709603","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"mallorys_camera","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://mallorys-camera.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25709603,"talkid":100428,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25709603#t25709603","above":25708579,"upictitle":"Every Day Above Ground: pic#110588672","article":"&gt;&gt;He was the problem child&lt;&lt;<br /><br />Definitely!  :-)  <br /><br />But don't you think all three in their respective ways were problem children?  :-)  I'll bet a <u>lot</u> of editing went into <i>This Side of Paradise</i>.<br /><br />And I've always wondered how much editing was involved with Ernest Hemingway...<br /><br />Wouldn't it be <u>great</u> to discover that Hemingway wrote, \"You know, there are a lot of really awful things in the world.  It's a really tough place!  The world, I mean.  Even if you're a <u>nice</u> guy!  Sooner or later, you're just going to get it.  Kabang!  And there's absolutely nothing you can do about it.  Nothing.  Nada!  So why even bother trying to being good or gentle or brave?\"<br /><br />And that it was <u>Perkins</u> who transformed it to \"The world breaks everyone and afterward many are strong in the broken places. But those that will not break it kills. It kills the very good and the very gentle and the very brave impartially. If you are none of these you can be sure it will kill you too but there will be no special hurry.\"  :-)<br /><br />(Kinda like Raymond Carver and Gordon Lish.)<br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"February 1 2017, 19:14:08 UTC","parent":25708579,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://mallorys-camera.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"mallorys_camera","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"mallorys_camera","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://mallorys-camera.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"mallorys_camera","ctime_ts":1485976448,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25707043#t25707043","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25707043#t25707043","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25707043#t25707043","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"srdrbr","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://srdrbr.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25707043,"talkid":100418,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519459.html?thread=25707043#t25707043","upictitle":"srdrbr: pic#0","article":"I'm glad you watched this amazing movie.<br /><br />I watched it few months ago, I had to, it checked so many boxes on my promising movie list. It is period piece, check, it is about writers, check, it stars Jude Law (whom I like immensely ever since Gattaca), check, it stars Colin Firth (another favorite of mine, he was brilliant in say, A Single Man, watch it if you haven't), check.<br /><br />Genius really was quite an experience, the sort of movie which is deeply impactful, but non the less overshadowed by constant stream of blockbusters.<br /><br />Oscars proved not to be really up to task of judging the movies and proclaiming the best, but again I am generally negatively disposed to award ceremonies, so your opinion may differ.<br /><br />Next time when I recommend Genius to somebody I will mentioned it was endorsed by George R.R. Martin to add weight to my own recommendation :)","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"February 1 2017, 17:57:58 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Genius","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://srdrbr.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"srdrbr","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"srdrbr","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://srdrbr.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"srdrbr","ctime_ts":1485971878,"tracked":0},{"shown":0,"collapsed":1,"uname":"laviniagrace","loaded":0,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://laviniagrace.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.l